<br>
Planes raids<br>
-------------<br>
Ex. 1: Valoran member (a guild that used to do Plane of Fear/Plane of Hate Raids all on their own, without any other guilds, i.e. not in an alliance) can sign up for planes raids sponsored by the Council of Guilds, but are not to take the place of members of guilds from ex. 2 or 3 below unless we need a specific class (such as clerics, monks, enchanters, rogues, or warriors) and none are available from Ex. 2 and ex. 3<br>
Ex. 2: Haven of Light member (a guild that currently does planes raids, but they do it as part of an alliance) CAN and SHOULD sign up for a planes raid sponsored by the Council of Guilds<br>
Ex. 3: Mist Walkers member (a guild that does not currently do planes raids either by itself or in an alliance) CAN and SHOULD sign up for planes raids sponsored by the Council of Guilds<br>
<br>
Dragon Raids<br>
------------<br>
Ex. 1 Grey Hawke member (a guild that is in the dragon rotation by itself) should not sign up for dragon raids sponsored by the Council of Guilds<br>
Ex. 2 Sign of One member (a guild that is in the dragon rotation in an alliance with Silent Watch) can sign up for dragon (Vox and Nagafen) raids sponsored by the Council of Guilds<br>
Ex. 3 Mist Walkers member (a guild that is not currently in the dragon rotation either by itself or in an alliance) CAN and SHOULD sign up for Council of Guilds dragon raids<br>
<br>
ALL OTHER Council of Guilds Events<br>
----------------------------------<br>
Unless specified by the organizer, ALL other CoG events are open to ANY of the above examples<br>
<br>
Please keep in mind, the Council of Guilds DOES so much MORE than just planes and dragon raids. They just happen to be what most people seem to fixate on, but it's really just a small portion of what we do.<br>
<br>
Haemish MacLennan<br>
